      • range

        @NotNull
public static <N extends Number> Consumer<Channel<N,?>> range(@NotNull
                                                                       N start,
                                                                       @NotNull
                                                                       N end)
        Returns a consumer generating the specified range of data.
        The stream will generate a range of numbers up to and including the end element, by applying a default increment of +1 or -1 depending on the comparison between the first and the last element. That is, if the first element is less than the last, the increment will be +1. On the contrary, if the former is greater than the latter, the increment will be -1.
        Type Parameters:
        N - the number type.
        Parameters:
        start - the first element of the range.
        end - the last element of the range.
        Returns:
        the consumer instance.

        Returns a consumer generating the specified sequence of data.
        The generated data will start from the specified first and will produce the specified number of elements, by computing each next one through the specified function.
        Type Parameters:
        DATA - the data type.
        Parameters:
        start - the first element of the sequence.
        count - the number of generated elements.
        nextFunction - the function computing the next element.
        Returns:
        the consumer instance.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the count is not positive.
